<section id="fs-idm6682304" class="critical-thinking">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-idp3444976">
<problem id="fs-idm192500320">
<para id="fs-idm146803824">Deregulation, like all changes in government policy, always has pluses and minuses. What do you think some of the minuses might be for airline deregulation?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idp16621792">
<problem id="fs-idm67112480">
<para id="fs-idm9976336">Do you think it is possible for government to outlaw everything that businesses could do wrong? If so, why does government not do that? If not, how can regulation stay ahead of rogue businesses that push the limits of the system until it breaks?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
