<definition id="fs-idp95439616">
<term>regulatory capture</term><meaning id="fs-idp41058576">when the firms supposedly being regulated end up playing a large role in setting the regulations that they will follow and as a result, they “capture” the people doing the regulation, usually through the promise of a job in that “regulated” industry once their term in government has ended.</meaning>
